---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="PhD" description="Friends or Foes: Does polarisation really undermine democracy?">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>PhD research</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DISSERTATION INFO + BOOK COVER -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px; gap: 3rem; align-items: start;">
        <div>
          <p class="section__label">Dissertation</p>
          <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Friends or Foes: Does polarisation really undermine democracy?</h2>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            Understanding the two-way relationship between polarisation dynamics and the processes and institutions of democratic contestation.
          </p>

          <div class="info-grid" style="margin-bottom: 0;">
            <div>
              <p class="info-grid__label">Institutions</p>
              <p class="info-grid__value">Vrije Universiteit Brussel<br>University of Warwick</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="info-grid__label">Supervisors</p>
              <p class="info-grid__value">Didier Caluwaerts (VUB)<br>Michael Saward (Warwick)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="info-grid__label">Funder</p>
              <p class="info-grid__value">EUTOPIA Co-tutelle PhD<br>Scholarship 2021–2025</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="/images/Cover.png" alt="PhD dissertation Kamil Bernaerts, cover painting by Hazel Van Hove" style="width: 100%; border-radius: 4px; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);" />
          <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-top: 0.5rem; text-align: center;">VUBPRESS, 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABSTRACT -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Abstract</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; max-width: 680px;">
        My PhD examined the two-way relationship between polarisation and democracy. On the one hand, I investigated whether and how different forms of polarisation — especially affective polarisation — undermine democratic attitudes and behaviours. On the other hand, I explored how democratic institutions and processes shape polarisation dynamics, asking whether some institutional designs are better at containing the harmful consequences of polarisation than others.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; max-width: 680px;">
        In doing so, I combined theoretical advancement of the concept of polarisation with extensive empirical analysis, drawing on cross-national comparative data spanning 113 democracies over more than a century, as well as original survey-experimental data from Belgium and the United Kingdom.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; max-width: 680px;">
        The dissertation challenges the common assumption that polarisation is inherently harmful to democracy. Instead, it shows that the relationship is conditional: certain forms of polarisation, under certain institutional conditions, can coexist with — and even strengthen — democratic processes. The boundary between healthy democratic conflict and harmful polarisation depends on whether the polarisation involves mere disagreement, active dislike, or deeper negative emotions like hatred and contempt.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BOOK + DEFENCE PHOTO -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 2.5rem; align-items: start;">
        <div>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Book</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.75;">
            The dissertation has been published as a monograph by <strong style="font-weight: 500;">VUBPRESS</strong> (2025). 
            Read a <a href="https://plc-journal.eu/article/view/25310" target="_blank" rel="noopener">published summary</a> or 
            <a href="https://plc-journal.eu/article/view/25455" target="_blank" rel="noopener">published review</a> in <em>Politics of the Low Countries</em>. 
            A Dutch press release can be found <a href="https://press.vub.ac.be/polarisatie-bedreiging-of-motor-voor-democratie" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img src="/images/defense.JPG" alt="PhD defence at Vrije Universiteit Brussel, September 2025" style="width: 100%; border-radius: 4px;" />
          <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-top: 0.5rem;">Public defence, September 15, 2025, VUB.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
